AUTOSAR, the LIN slave refers to the communication protocol used by the vehicles electronic systems to communicate with other devices on the LIN (Local Interconnect Network) network. The LIN slave is responsible for receiving and transmitting data on the LIN bus, and is typically implemented on non-AUTOSAR MCUs (Microcontrollers Units) or other electronic control units (ECUs) within the vehicle. The LIN slave follows the LIN 2.1 specification and conforms to the ISO 17987 standard. Its functionality, including wake-up functionality, is covered by the LIN Interface, LIN driver, and LIN transceiver driver within the MCAL AUTOSAR framework.\n <br><br>**Reference documents:**\n- <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:2234/files/AUTOSAR!R4.3.1!AUTOSAR_SWS_LINInterface.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AUTOSAR/R4.3.1/AUTOSAR_SWS_LINInterface.pdf</a>  .Page |9\n- <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:2234/files/AUTOSAR!R21-11!AUTOSAR_SRS_LIN.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AUTOSAR/R21-11/AUTOSAR_SRS_LIN.pdf</a>  .Page |10\n- <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:2234/files/AUTOSAR!R21-11!AUTOSAR_SWS_LINInterface.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AUTOSAR/R21-11/AUTOSAR_SWS_LINInterface.pdf</a>  .Page |11\n\n ',2), (909,216,'Ask for information about the document','You have chosen option **Ask for information about the document**',NULL),(910,216,'AUTOSAR','You have chosen option **Ask for information about the document -> AUTOSAR**',1);
